File: All provinces are urged to watch their numbers and quickly ensure contact tracing and quarantine. AFP/Phill Magakoe JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize is sounding the alarm about rising coronavirus infections. He's concerned about a 9 percent increase countrywide in the last week. READ: COVID-19: SA reports 164 deaths, 1,050 new infections Of particular concern, is the Western Cape. There, new infections have grown 42 percent in seven days. READ: Dr Zweli Mkhize tests positive for COVID-19 Mkhize says the spike appears mostly to be linked to a super-spreader event at a bar. All provinces are urged to watch their numbers and quickly ensure contact tracing and quarantine. Mkhize says he himself is recovering well from COVID-19 and his wife is home from hospital.